After appointment, letters shall be issued to the personal representative by the register. Letters shall contain:
The name and location of the court or register by whom appointment was made;
The name of the decedent and the personal representative;
The date of his appointment;
The date of probate of the will admitted to probate in the proceeding;
The signature of the register and the seal of the court; and
Date certificate was issued.
